Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a @salt{pinch}. When boiling,
stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @Star Anise{1/2} and cook for
~{25%minutes}.

> TIP: Add more water if it starts to evaporate too much.

When cooked, drain the rice thoroughly in a #sieve{} and return to the saucepan,
off the heat. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel and grate the
@ginger{1}. Halve the @Bell Pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and chop
into small pieces. Chop the @Baby Corn{60} in half lengthways. Trim the
@Green Beans{150%g}(trimmed) and chop in half. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion, stir
and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the ginger, @Yellow Thai Style Paste{12.5%g}
(add less if you don't like things too hot!) and @honey{7.5%ml} and cook, stirring, for
~{1%minute} more. Add the green beans, pepper and @Light Coconut Milk{400%ml}. Stir
together, then simmer until thickened, ~{10%minutes}. Stir in the baby corn
for the last ~{5%minutes}.

While the curry cooks, trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice. Zest the
@lime{1} and chop into wedges.

When the curry is cooked, stir through the @soy sauce{12.5%ml} and add a squeeze
of lime juice. Taste and add more lime juice if desired. Fluff up the rice with
a #fork{} and remove the star anise, then stir through the spring onion and
lime zest.